Define Function to Return Stock Data¶

In [3]:
def fetch_data(symbol:str, name: str):
    quotes = yf.Ticker(symbol).history(start = "2016-01-01") # Fetch Stock Quotes from Yahoo Finance
    fundamentals = fin.get_fundamentals(name) # Fetch Fundamentals from Finanzen.net
    estimates = fin.get_estimates(name) # Fetch Estimates from Finanzen.net
    return {"Quotes": quotes, "Fundamentals": fundamentals, "Estimates": estimates}

Filter Quotes Data to most recent Start Date¶

In [5]:
# Find most recent Start Date
start_dates = []
for x in stock_data:
    start_dates.append(stock_data[x]["Quotes"].index.min())

start_date = start_dates[0]
for x in start_dates:
    if x > start_date:
        start_date = x

Join all Quote DataFrames¶

In [6]:
# Init Master DataFrame
df_list = []

# Add all Quotes DataFrames to Master
for x in stock_data:
    df_tmp = stock_data[x]["Quotes"].reset_index()[["Date", "Close"]]
    df_tmp["Stock"] = x
    df_tmp = df_tmp[df_tmp["Date"] >= start_date]
    start_value = df_tmp.iloc[0]["Close"]
    df_tmp["Performance"] = df_tmp["Close"] / start_value
    df_tmp["Rolling STD"] = df_tmp["Performance"].rolling(30).std()
    df_list.append(df_tmp)
    
# Join Dataframes
quote_df = pd.concat(df_list)

Classify Stocks by Performance¶

In [7]:
# Compute Total Performance and Group in Quantiles
performance_total = pd.DataFrame(quote_df.groupby("Stock")["Performance"].last() - 1).reset_index()
performance_quantiles = performance_total["Performance"].quantile([.20, .40, .60, .80])

# Classify by Quantiles
performance_total["PClass"] = "Low-End"
performance_total.loc[(performance_total["Performance"] >= performance_quantiles[0.2]) & 
                      (performance_total["Performance"] < performance_quantiles[0.4]), "PClass"] = "Low"
performance_total.loc[(performance_total["Performance"] >= performance_quantiles[0.4]) & 
                      (performance_total["Performance"] < performance_quantiles[0.6]), "PClass"] = "Median"
performance_total.loc[(performance_total["Performance"] >= performance_quantiles[0.6]) & 
                      (performance_total["Performance"] < performance_quantiles[0.8]), "PClass"] = "High"
performance_total.loc[(performance_total["Performance"] >= performance_quantiles[0.8]), "PClass"] = "High-End"

# Join Data
quote_df = pd.merge(quote_df, performance_total[["Stock", "PClass"]], "left", "Stock").\
              sort_values(["Stock", "Date"])

Correlation Matrix (Performance)¶

# Calculate Difference in Performance
quote_df["Performance_diff"] = quote_df.groupby("Stock")["Performance"].diff()

# Calculate Matrix of absolute Correlation Coefficient
performance_matrix = quote_df.pivot(index='Date', columns='Stock', values='Performance_diff').corr().abs()

# Plot Heatmap
sns.heatmap(performance_matrix.corr().abs(), cmap = "Greens")
plt.show()

def plot_std(PClass: str):
    global quote_df
    sns.relplot(x="Date", y="Rolling STD",
                col="Stock", legend="full", 
                data=quote_df[quote_df["PClass"] == PClass],
                kind="line", col_wrap = 3)
    plt.ylim(0, max_std)
    plt.show()

Plot Fundamentals¶

In [21]:
# Define Function to Collect Fundamenstals
def collect_fundamentals(stock_data, key):
    df_list = []
    for x in stock_data:
        df_tmp = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(stock_data[x]["Fundamentals"][key], 
                                    orient = "index").transpose()
        df_tmp["Stock"] = x
        df_list.append(df_tmp)

    result_df = pd.concat(df_list).reset_index().rename(columns = {"index": "Year"})
    result_df["Year"] = pd.to_datetime(result_df["Year"], format='%Y')
    result_df = result_df.sort_values(["Stock", "Year"])
    return result_df
    

# Collect Data
key_ratios = collect_fundamentals(stock_data, "Key Ratios")
income = collect_fundamentals(stock_data, "Income Statement")

# Join Performance Class
key_ratios = pd.merge(key_ratios, performance_total[["Stock", "PClass"]], "left", "Stock")
income = pd.merge(income, performance_total[["Stock", "PClass"]], "left", "Stock")
